OL,3,CEx-police officer holds back tears as
OL,4,Che recalls impact of Novichok poisoning
OL,6,FMr Bailey frequently referred to his
OL,7,Fwitness statement throughout his
OL,8,Fevidence and recalled a colleague
OL,9,Fcalling the control room to say "a
OL,10,FRussian spy has been poisoned".
OL,12,FHe told the inquiry: "It is not
OL,13,Fsomething that I had heard before and
OL,14,Fit's not something I had thought I
OL,15,Fwould ever hear again.
OL,17,F"It was a bizarre incident.
OL,19,F"I remember thinking 'I will never
OL,20,Fhear that phrase on a Wiltshire Police
OL,21,Fradio again'."
