OL,3,CEx-police officer holds back tears as
OL,4,Che recalls impact of Novichok poisoning
OL,6,F"Once I turned the lights on,
OL,7,Feverything was crystal clear and it
OL,8,Fwas juddered as opposed to being a
OL,9,Fsmooth motion of looking around.
OL,11,F"It was almost in frames ` it was
OL,12,Fquite scary."
OL,14,FThe inquiry chairman Lord Hughes
OL,15,Fconcluded Mr Bailey's evidence by
OL,16,Fsaying: "I am very conscious you have
OL,17,Fhad to relive a very nasty experience
OL,18,Fbut it was necessary and thank you for
OL,19,Fdoing it."
OL,21,FThe inquiry continues.
